		<value>Causes may include:  - A type of anemia in which red blood cells in the blood are destroyed earlier than normal (hemolytic anemia)  - Anemia due to low iron  - After certain infections, major surgery or trauma, or allergic reactions  - Cancer  - Certain medicines  - Bone marrow disease called polycythemia vera  - Bone marrow making too many platelets without a known cause (primary thrombocythemia)  - Recent spleen removal    Some people with high platelet counts may be at risk of forming blood clots.</value>
